last_episode_to_air.name: A Shoulder To Lean On
last_episode_to_air.overview: A pedestrian is rushed to A&E with multiple life-threatening injuries after being injured in a hit-and-run. An acrobat has a damaged wrist. A 93-year-old has a broken leg.

name: 24 Hours in A&E
overview: A British medical documentary set in King's College Hospital. 91 cameras filmed round the clock for 28 days, 24 hours a day in A&E it offers unprecedented access to one of Britain's busiest A&E departments.

seasons.name: Season 30
seasons.overview: The award-winning show returns - this time in Nottingham and Queen's Medical Centre, one of the busiest A&Es in Europe.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Kofi, who is 11, is rushed into resus, critically injured after being hit by a van. Roger, 73, is attempting to come to terms with his own mortality.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Alex, 19, has badly injured his hand punching a window. 31-year-old motorcyclist Brendan has had a head-on collision with a car. Pat, who is 78, has broken her arm.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Chris Lacy finds himself being tested to the limits after three trauma patients arrive in quick succession. One of them has been shot in the face, another has been stabbed in the chest and a third has been knifed in his head.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: 39-year-old Sean has had too much to drink and has ended up tripping over a clothes horse and broken his neck.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Peggy, who is 89, is rushed in with a suspected stroke. Sally has sliced her finger opening a jar. Charlie, 60, is back for the second time in a week after previously being discharged following a crash.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: 35-year-old Colin has been stabbed by a home intruder. Nancy, 87, collapsed at home, where she lives alone. And Robert, a former lawyer who's lost his family and home to alcoholism, is brought to A&E very drunk.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Working a 12-hour night shift the team have to treat some young men with stab wounds and as their friends wait in the A&E waiting room the tension begins to increase.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: 22-year-old Claire is in A&E after being knocked off her bike. 73-year-old John is admitted after a routine health screening revealed a potentially-deadly abdominal aortic aneurysm. 92-year-old Eileen has fallen and spent the night on the floor at home.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: Colin, 32, has been attacked with a knife and cut his arm. Father and son Morris and Colin sustain life-threatening injuries from gatecrashers to their family party. Catherine, 21, lost consciousness at a party.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: William has broken his leg in three places, after being crushed by a cherry picker. Nick has fallen from a 10-metre ladder onto concrete. Darren has put his arm through a window while cleaning it.

episodes.name: Episode 11
episodes.overview: Stuart, 59, has come into A&E with a suspected heart attack. 78-year-old Reginald has a life-threatening gut condition. Richard has twisted his knee moon-walking in a club.

episodes.name: Episode 12
episodes.overview: Staff at King's battle to save an 18-year-old who's been stabbed in a street fight. Omar, who is 88, is brought into A&E after experiencing severe stomach pains. Hany has tried to overdose on drugs.

episodes.name: Episode 13
episodes.overview: 74-year-old Ted and his wife Irene are in the A&E department for the tenth time this year. Ted is suffering with terminal bladder cancer, but his condition has got much worse.

episodes.name: Episode 14
episodes.overview: Clive, who is 61 and an alcoholic, has come in with a suspected stroke. Joseph, 16, has had a stroke after collapsing at school. A regular patient who suffers from schizophrenia is admitted for the 19th time in a year.

episodes.name: Rush Hour
episodes.overview: Christopher and Sarah come into A&E, from separate cycling accidents. Kevin, 40, has fallen three metres from scaffolding onto his head. 80-year-old Bill's legs gave way while he was in a working men's club.

episodes.name: Young Ones
episodes.overview: 16-year-old Ellie has been thrown from her horse and crushed against a fence. Destiny, 4, has a fish bone stuck in his throat. Jill, who is 36, is losing a lot of blood while seven weeks pregnant.

episodes.name: Code Red
episodes.overview: Trauma consultant Simon has to deal with a busy night, with many critically ill and seriously injured patients. He also has to deal with the fallout from an extraordinary night of violence on London's streets.

episodes.name: Allergic to Pain
episodes.overview: Jim, 50, has a dislocated shoulder that takes a five-strong team to pull back into place. A 30-year-old has broken his toe when he kicked a concrete block thinking it was a football. Alan, who is 63, is worried he might have deep vein thrombosis in his one remaining leg. 83-year-old James has a cyst on his knee that has left him housebound. Rose, 91, has had a suspected stroke.

episodes.name: Vital Organs
episodes.overview: 19-year-old fitness fanatic Josh shows up at the hospital badly injured after a canal barge accident. Liam, 21, has a sore finger following a night's clubbing. Jean, who is 80 and has terminal cancer, has collapsed at home.

episodes.name: One Moment In Time
episodes.overview: 21-year-old Danielle is in A&E unable to walk with swollen legs, and doctors are worried about her kidneys. Aaron, 16, has fallen from a second-floor balcony onto concrete. Latoya, who is 34, has cut her head during a night out with friends.

episodes.name: A Good Life
episodes.overview: William, who is 83, has sliced his finger doing metalwork. Ernest, 93, shows up with life-threatening injuries after being knocked over by a hit and run driver just outside the hospital. 52-year-old Kevin has a history of heart problems and collapsed at home.

episodes.name: Saturday Night
episodes.overview: Pharrell, who is 8, has fallen from a ramp at a BMX park onto his face. 18-year-old Dalvin has crashed his motorbike into a bollard at 35 mph, with a nasty injury to his thigh. Clodagh, 34, tumbled down concrete steps at a wake, breaking her arm. A stabbing victim comes in with the knife still in place.

episodes.name: Mum
episodes.overview: Josephine, who is 71 and terminally ill with cancer, has been brought into the hospital suffering with chronic breathing difficulties. Sara, who is recovering from cancer, has been bitten by her cat. Marcia has hurt her wrist while slipping on the stairs. 5-year-old Olivia has banged her head on a glass coffee table.

episodes.name: We Are Family
episodes.overview: James, who is 22 and a chef, accidentally stabbed himself in the thigh while chopping tomatoes at work. Bernard, 54, has been rushed to resus after falling and banging his head. 83-year-old Ruby collapsed with severe knee pain.

episodes.name: Snow
episodes.overview: 5-year-old Daisy is rushed into resus after her skirt caught alight on a gas fire at home. Her dad Damien, who came in the ambulance with her, has badly burnt his hands putting out the flames. Maurice, 74, tripped and hurt his hand. Ginger, who is 61, has been bitten by her cat, resulting in an infected hand.

episodes.name: The 'Q' Word
episodes.overview: Cyclist Alun, 32, has come off his bike at 30 mph. Baby Jaziah has been rushed to resus with breathing difficulties. 18-month-old Charlie is struggling to give a urine sample. Ronald, who is 81, has had a suspected stroke.

episodes.name: Cause Unknown
episodes.overview: 9-year-old Tino is rushed to resus after slumping over her desk at school and not being able to remember her name, who people are, or where she is. Karen has been experiencing numbness down her left side and requires a scan. Bailey, 11, has been hit by a car on his way home from school and broken his leg.

episodes.name: Life's Little Hiccups
episodes.overview: 37-year-old Stacey, who previously has had a collapsed lung, is experiencing breathing difficulties. Andrew, who is 26 and a bodybuilder, has been knocked off his motorbike by a car. Henry has been hiccuping for three days. 20-year-old student Sam has been kicked and punched in the head outside a nightclub.

episodes.name: Brief Encounter
episodes.overview: Suzanne fights for her life after being punched by a stranger and hitting her head on the kerb. 90-year-old Frank has been brought to resus after his wife found him collapsed at home. Tom, who is 12, is brought in from Kent by helicopter after being hit by a car.

episodes.name: Three Sisters
episodes.overview: 80-year-old Rose has fluid on her lungs and is having trouble breathing. 55-year-old trucker Kevin has serious injuries after his lorry rolled down a verge.

episodes.name: Reality Check
episodes.overview: Neil is flown in by helicopter after a head-on road collision. Matias needs help after trapping his hands in a train door and being dragged along the platform.

episodes.name: Valentine's Day
episodes.overview: John, who is 53, has crashed his motorbike but doesn't want to worry his partner, who's on holiday. 52-year-old Gary has a bleed on the brain. Ronald, 84, has been bitten by his dog.

episodes.name: Second Chance
episodes.overview: The show this week takes a look at people suffering with head injuries and the power of unconditional love.

episodes.name: Head First
episodes.overview: The parents of a young girl who fell dangerously at a local diving pool are worried. We also take a look at the work of the hospital's security team.

episodes.name: Walk Like A Man
episodes.overview: Nicholas, 26, has been punched in the face, fracturing and dislocating his jaw. 33-year-old Simon dislocated his kneecap playing rugby. Tyrell, who is 17, has damaged his big toe playing football. Amoui, 78, was found collapsed in her flat.

episodes.name: No Regrets
episodes.overview: Gary, 47, has been flown to King's by air ambulance after his motorbike hit a car. Steve, 69, has got a fish bone stuck in his finger while trying to impress a female friend.

episodes.name: Live & Let Live
episodes.overview: Thomas has been struck on the back of the head by a six-metre pole at a building site in South London. Hilton has diabetes and is concerned about his swollen legs.

episodes.name: Love & Pain
episodes.overview: Ahmed has dislocated his shoulder whilst playing a game of American football and has to grit his teeth as doctor Matt puts it back into place. Dad-of-four Simon hasn't eaten for days after his partner ended their relationship.

episodes.name: Duty of Care
episodes.overview: 94-year-old Douglas has been brought to hospital because his breathing has deteriorated.

episodes.name: For Better or Worse
episodes.overview: Husbands and wives reflect on their enduring marriages and the changing nature of love. The A&E staff discuss wisdom and experience.

episodes.name: Mothers & Sons
episodes.overview: The series takes a look at the challenges of motherhood and the responsibility of raising sons this week.

episodes.name: Under the Influence
episodes.overview: Kevin, 57, has fallen off a ladder and landed on a sharp metal bar. John, 53, has fallen down a flight of steps. Ross, 31, has fallen and hit his head while on a night out. Eleven-year-old Archie has fallen up a step at the school library and has badly cut his lip.

episodes.name: A Few Good Men
episodes.overview: Tony, who is 59 and a delivery driver, is airlifted to King's from Kent, after being badly hurt in a head-on road traffic collision. Eric, 85, has ongoing stomach problems. 79-year-old Jim is having difficulty breathing. A patient brought in by police tries to escape.

episodes.name: Grin and Bear It
episodes.overview: The show takes a look the different ways that people deal with pain and how the care and support of friends and family can help you get through nearly anything.

episodes.name: Tough Love
episodes.overview: Mark, who is 31 and has advanced multiple sclerosis, has developed a fever. 65-year-old Christine is brought into King's by her friends after collapsing while playing bingo. Jean, 20, is homeless and was assaulted five days ago.

episodes.name: Twilight
episodes.overview: Graham, 75, has been attacked. Mum Cheryl has two poorly boys.

episodes.name: Night Shift
episodes.overview: The week the cameras follow a busy Saturday night in the A&E Department where staff have to deal with the needs of elderly patients and sick children as well as patients who are drunk or violent.

episodes.name: Life Blood
episodes.overview: A young girl is brought in who has been seriously injured having been run over by a bus with other pedestrians who were also hit. 12-year-old Jade from Kent is rushed to the hospital after being hit by a car and knocked under a bus while walking to school.

episodes.name: Worst Case Scenario
episodes.overview: Arthur, who is 79, has stomach pains but isn't one to complain. Tom, 20, is having trouble breathing.

episodes.name: Life in the Fast Lane
episodes.overview: Pauline, 70, is brought to A&E with two broken legs after being hit by a car that swerved off the road. 11-year-old Scarlett has been knocked down by a car travelling 30 mph at a zebra crossing. Steve, who is 48, has been transferred from Kent, after blacking out and crashing while driving at 70 mph on a motorway.

episodes.name: Love Hurts
episodes.overview: 19-month-old baby Xah'nae has been vomiting, is suffering with a high fever and has become floppy and unresponsive. 52-year-old Graham, who has Down's syndrome and dementia, hit his head when he fell over in his bathroom. Christine, 61, has been rushed to A&E after collapsing unconscious at her sister's house.

episodes.name: One Day at a Time
episodes.overview: Bill, 92, has a swollen leg and is struggling to breathe. Andy, 45, has stomach cramps.

episodes.name: Remember Me
episodes.overview: Peggy, who is 85, is brought in by ambulance after falling over at home and hurt her knee. Ben's swollen finger is more serious than he realises.

episodes.name: Mum's the Word
episodes.overview: Eddie, who is 12, has been hit by a car, his fourth visit to A&E on a blue light. Linda, who is 64, has had respiratory failure.

episodes.name: Next of Kin
episodes.overview: Stacie, 38, has fallen out of a tree onto her head. Ashleigh, who is 19, is rushed in after being involved in a high-speed, head-on car crash. Peter, 78, has abdominal pains.

episodes.name: A Time to Laugh
episodes.overview: 2-year-old Cydney's parents have brought her into King's as she hasn't passed urine for two days. Dilson, 33, is rushed in suffering with severe knife wounds after being stabbed in the head and neck as he attempted to stop a fight outside a nightclub. 79-year-old Doreen has had a fall at home and injured her wrist.

episodes.name: Pick Me Up
episodes.overview: Pat, who is 71 and has a history of brain haemorrhages, is brought in after being found unconscious at home. 63-year-old Mick was found lying in the street with severe head injuries. Graham, 50, is rushed to King's after having a suspected heart attack. Chris, 21, has chest pains and has been coughing up blood.

episodes.name: Luck of the Draw
episodes.overview: Alyce, who is 89, is brought to King's after falling near her home. Sean, who is 23, is rushed in after having a seizure that lasted most of the night.

episodes.name: Wake Up Call
episodes.overview: Phil, 36, has chronic pain in his back and side. Kamilla, 12, has been knocked down by a car. Malcolm is rushed in the hospital after suffering a cardiac arrest, and is on life support.

episodes.name: City of Angels
episodes.overview: Consultant Graham thinks Icylyn's bloated abdomen could be due to something serious.

episodes.name: The Fall
episodes.overview: Fitness instructor Jeremy has had an accident on his bicycle and injured his wrist. Rienelle, who is 7, has fallen 2 metres from the top of a climbing frame onto her back. 48-year-old Bobby has been brought to King's after he suffered seizures at home. Ronald, 70, has been rushed into A&E suffering from acute breathing difficulties and possible kidney failure.

episodes.name: Amongst Friends
episodes.overview: Registrar Ling has just began her shift and her friend Claire is working alongside her. David is brought into the hospital having seizures uncontrollably for 30 minutes.

episodes.name: Bolt from the Blue
episodes.overview: Kevin, who is 78, is rushed to A&E after going into cardiac arrest while exercising. Monica, who is 83 and has osteoporosis, has been rushed to King's after falling at home.

episodes.name: Stand By Me
episodes.overview: Four-year-old Alfie is brought into the hospital with a broken thighbone having fallen off his bike. The team are worried that Alfie might have ruptured an artery, causing some internal bleeding.

episodes.name: Young at Heart
episodes.overview: 72-year-old Laura has come to King's after suffering a suspected stroke. Nic, who is 47 and the UK's over-40s BMX champion, visits A&E after falling 20 feet when a stunt went wrong. Marjorie, 83, has pain behind her eye following a recent bout of shingles.

episodes.name: Going the Distance
episodes.overview: Brian, who is 74 and has dementia, is taken to King's by ambulance after falling down a flight of stairs.

episodes.name: Resilience
episodes.overview: Ellen has taken a fall and has lost a lot of blood. Toddler Zara has some Lego up her nose.

episodes.name: Throw of the Dice
episodes.overview: Linden, 15, is at King's after cutting his leg backflipping off a shed onto a trampoline. And Antony - who has smoked for 40 years - has lost all feeling in his left leg.

episodes.name: Family Matters
episodes.overview: Builder Jamie is rushed in to A&E after falling from the roof of a three-storey building. 80-year-old Daphne has dislocated her replacement hip while putting on her socks. 4-month-old Weston has been brought to paediatric A&E after suffering from diarrhoea and vomiting for over 24 hours.

episodes.name: Boys Don't Cry
episodes.overview: 16-year-old Max is brought to King's by air ambulance after falling 14 feet in a skate park. Hector, who is 13, injured his hip playing football.

episodes.name: One Fine Day
episodes.overview: At St George's in south west London, the trauma team fight to save the life of a young woman after a motorbike accident. Luke, who is 11, is brought in after having a seizure.

episodes.name: Seize the Day
episodes.overview: Dave, 53, has crashed into a stationary car while riding his bicycle, and has a significant facial injury. 30-year-old Richard has come into A&E after dislocating his thumb while cycling. Billy, a 19-year-old motocross rider, has been thrown off his bike during a race and suffered multiple spinal fractures.

episodes.name: Someone to Love
episodes.overview: Paul, who is 38 and a tree surgeon, is rushed into resus after falling 25 feet from a tree. Anthony, who was recently diagnosed with Parkinson's and prostate cancer, has fallen down some stairs.

episodes.name: Stay with Me
episodes.overview: When 70-year-old John dislocates his shoulder while out running, the St George's staff put him on ketamine for the pain, and the side effects keep his wife entertained.

episodes.name: Bouncing Back
episodes.overview: 60-year-old Iain is rushed to St George's after falling 10 feet off a ladder. 13-year-old Lucy has lost the feeling in her feet and hands after falling off a trampoline.

episodes.name: Strong Medicine
episodes.overview: 82-year-old Rusty has been hit by a car and has a broken ankle. Mihhail, who is 29, has crashed his motorcycle into a bollard.

episodes.name: Chip off the Block
episodes.overview: 7-year-old Freddie is brought to St George's after falling several metres from a tree in his garden. Martin, 66, has collapsed at home and is suffering from poor eyesight and dizziness.

episodes.name: In a Heartbeat
episodes.overview: Retired builder Roger has fallen four metres from his daughter's roof. Tad, who is 29, has come to St George's with a dangerously high heart rate, which could possibly lead to a stroke.

episodes.name: Modern Families
episodes.overview: Will, 13, gets a CT scan for head injuries sustained in a baseball accident. Baby Amira has an irregular heartbeat. Chris, who is 21 and a pizza delivery rider, has been knocked off his motorbike.

episodes.name: Addicted to Love
episodes.overview: Carole, 45, is brought to A&E after experiencing chest pains and collapsing. Dinner lady Collette has cut her finger while chopping vegetables. Lucy, who is 25 and has intercranial hypertension, is suffering from a severe headache. Philip, who is 53, is rushed in following a seizure, and doctors suspect he may have had a stroke.

episodes.name: Every Minute Counts
episodes.overview: The staff at St George's tackle one of their most dramatic and unusual emergencies. Rail worker Alan has been hit by a high-speed train and is at risk of losing his right arm.

episodes.name: Do No Harm
episodes.overview: 11-month-old Isabel is rushed to St George's after suffering a fit and losing consciousness. 22-year-old Felix is brought to A&E with a self-inflicted stab wound to his stomach. Retired engineer Bill, 68, arrives by air ambulance with breathing difficulties and suspected multiple fractures after falling 15 feet from a ladder while cutting a leylandii hedge.

episodes.name: No Place Like Home
episodes.overview: Peter, 85, has been brought - unwillingly - to A&E by his stepson Brian. He cut his finger on some wire two weeks earlier and his hand is swollen and won't stop bleeding. Emma, 23, is rushed to St George's after crashing her car on the way to her father's house, while doctors also see to 86-year-old Harry, who fell down a flight of stairs a day earlier but didn't seek treatment. Ciaran, 27, injured his ankle the previous night while out with friends and was given a temporary cast. Emergency nurse practitioner Helen needs to get him X-rayed and replastered, but he faces a return visit for an operation.

episodes.name: Free Spirit
episodes.overview: Tree surgeon David, 27, is airlifted to St George's after falling 40 feet to the ground, hitting several branches on his way down and landing head-first onto concrete. Anne, 74, arrives with a sharp pain in her chest. 51-year-old taxi driver Mark receives treatment for a cut on his finger caused by broken glass. 92-year-old Betty is brought in by ambulance after her carers found her with slurred speech and a shaking hand.

episodes.name: Emergency Landing
episodes.overview: Bob, 51, is airlifted to St George's after falling 20 feet from a ladder while repairing his roof. Retired pharmacologist Anthony, 68, receives help for a chronic gas problem. 83-year-old Gladys collapsed on the stairs at home and has a dangerously low heart rate.

episodes.name: Free Fall
episodes.overview: Robert, 9, has a dangerously high heart rate. Mark, 32, has fallen 30ft from scaffolding, and may have damaged his spine. Christine, 74, arrives in A&E after an accident in her garden, suffering nasty injuries to her face.

episodes.name: Force of Nature
episodes.overview: Becky, who is 59, is rushed in after a suspected stroke. Georgia, 19, fell 20 feet onto concrete trying to climb through a second-floor window after locking herself out of her flat. 88-year-old Edith is kept under observation after collapsing at home.

episodes.name: Don't Look Back
episodes.overview: Nikki, 50, and her mum Angela, 68, have been involved in a serious car crash. Ellen, 53, arrives with a painfully swollen elbow after falling over in a supermarket. 7-year-old Jack is rushed to A&E with an open fracture on his arm and a blow to his head after an accident at a wedding.

episodes.name: Guardian Angels
episodes.overview: Zaki, 63, has come to A&E after suffering a serious bleed following a tonsillectomy. Baby Amy has been rushed in after she stopped breathing at home. 21-year-old Craig fell 30 feet while motocross racing.

episodes.name: Soldier On
episodes.overview: Les, 40, is rushed to St George's after losing control of his car on a country road. Cambelle, who is 21, has an infected cyst that may require surgery. 67-year-old Patrick is brought to A&E after being dragged 40 metres by his horse and not found for two hours.

episodes.name: Look Forward
episodes.overview: Married couple Cora and Rae have multiple fractures after a road traffic collision. 23-year-old Scott, who was diagnosed with schizophrenia as a teenager, has badly cut his knee on a night out. Richard, 69, tripped and hit his head on the pavement.

episodes.name: Summer of Love
episodes.overview: This episode features people suffering misfortune while doing what they love, including a father and son who have been in a motorbike crash together, and a 14-year-old boy who has fallen from a tree.

episodes.name: The One
episodes.overview: 61-year-old Bill fell from the roof of his shed and has broken his neck. Chef Tony has burnt his legs when his barbecue exploded. Henry, 93, has severe breathing difficulties after experiencing a heart attack.

episodes.name: Never Too Late
episodes.overview: 82-year-old Barbara and her 80-year-old husband Clarence are brought into A&E after being knocked over by a motorbike. Actor Dudley has injured his shoulder rushing to catch a train. Isabel, 88, has come in with a swollen leg.

episodes.name: Take Care
episodes.overview: 76-year-old Margaret is rushed to St George's after showing signs of a stroke. Cyclist Sam, who is 13, is brought into A&E after falling off her bike at high speed during a race and landing on her head. Ursula, 84, is losing a concerning amount of blood from recurring nosebleeds.

episodes.name: Lean On Me
episodes.overview: Gerald, who is 66, has fallen from his loft and down two flights of stairs. 50-year-old Beverley arrives in A&E with an open fracture of her right leg after being hit by a car. Rubbish clearance worker Paul, 39, has sliced his arm on a ceramic tile.

episodes.name: Keep on Moving
episodes.overview: 70-year-old part-time DJ Tony arrives at St George's hospital after a high-speed bicycle accident. Cabin-crew worker Charlie, who is 39, has broken his arm in a scooter crash. Erin, 61, collapsed and has a debilitating ear infection.

episodes.name: Some Like It Hot
episodes.overview: Student George, 18, is sent for an urgent brain scan following a fight at a party. 28-year-old schoolteacher Niall has an ulcer on his eye after falling asleep with his contact lenses in. Doorman Alfred, who is 40, has been stabbed three times.

episodes.name: Father's Day
episodes.overview: 60-year-old diabetic Tony has an infected leg wound and must be assessed to ensure it doesn't spread. 3-year-old Billy has swollen eyes after accidentally squirting detergent in them. 80-year-old Ida has pain in her knee, and doctors are concerned when an X-ray reveals a shadow on her bone.

episodes.name: To Sir, With Love
episodes.overview: Sir John, 89, is brought to A&E with a suspected abdominal aortic aneurysm. 68-year-old Mick and his wife Linda have been involved in a head-on car crash. Niall, who is 10, has fallen out of a tree and broken his arm.

episodes.name: One Step At A Time
episodes.overview: 19-year-old motorcyclist Sam is airlifted to St George's with multiple injuries after crashing into a van and being thrown under a car. Raheem, 7,  arrives in A&E after cutting his wrist while playing at home. 59-year-old Therese turns up with a painful lump on her finger.

episodes.name: Always On My Mind
episodes.overview: Daisy, who is 22 months old, arrives at St George's Hospital by air ambulance after being kicked in the head by a horse. Mike, who is 54 and has epilepsy, arrives in minors with a bandage around his jaw after falling face-first onto the pavement. Florence, 100, arrives at the hospital suffering from what appears to be a stroke.

episodes.name: Give Me Strength
episodes.overview: 91-year-old Cyril is airlifted to hospital after a car crash which required him to be cut from his car. Caroline arrives at St Georges with chest pains. Roman, 5, has a pencil lead stuck in his ear.

episodes.name: Handle With Care
episodes.overview: Lawrence, 26, has been thrown 15 feet after being hit by a car while crossing the road. 53-year-old Katrina is having difficulty breathing and experiencing chest pains. Angela, who is 63, has been attacked by one of her cats as she shouted at a fox in her garden.

episodes.name: Out of Sight
episodes.overview: 10-year-old Josh has severed his finger at school. Stonemason Guido has dropped a slab of marble on his hand. 74-year-old partially-sighted Maggie is brought in by her neighbour after breaking her ankle in a fall.

episodes.name: First Impressions
episodes.overview: Mechanic Grant, 34, is rushed into A&E after being crushed against a brick wall by the car he was working on. 44-year-old Doug has a rare growth on his head and face which is prone to profuse bleeding. 23-year-old cage fighter Charlie is treated in minor injuries for something in his eye.

episodes.name: Brave Hearts
episodes.overview: 5-year-old Kayla is rushed into St George's struggling to breathe. Olivia, 12, has a nasty cut on her leg after attempting a handstand. Derek, who is 83, arrives in A&E in a confused state after falling over.

episodes.name: Independence Days
episodes.overview: 22-year-old motorcyclist Adam is brought into A&E after crashing into a car and being thrown 30 metres. A 78-year-old former nurse arrives in St George's after becoming dizzy at her sewing class, and doctors worry she has had a stroke. 18-year-old Rosa is treated after falling off her bike on the way home from a night out with friends.

episodes.name: Fathers and Sons
episodes.overview: 51-year-old builder Rod is rushed into A&E after falling 18 feet from scaffolding onto concrete. John, who is 86, is brought to St Georges with a head injury after falling off a wall. Cyclist Mack, 19, requires specialist help for a dislocated shoulder, after he collided with a Porsche.

episodes.name: Extra Time
episodes.overview: 74-year-old Derek is brought into A&E after suffering a suspected stroke. 31-year-old fireman Glenn arrives with a suspected abscess in his throat. Paula, 84, has a dangerously high level of potassium in her blood.

episodes.name: Glass Half Full
episodes.overview: 3-year-old Louie is airlifted to St George's after being run over by a car while playing outside. Josh, 14, has broken his ankle falling off the handlebars of the BMX his dad was riding. Sam, who is 41, arrives in resus with multiple injuries after losing control of her car and crashing into a tree.

episodes.name: Altered States
episodes.overview: A 79-year-old woman is brought in with signs of a stroke, and neurologist Dr Mahinda opts for a treatment that only has a slim chance of success. David, who is 77 and has type 1 diabetes, has an infection in his toes, and doctors consider amputating his foot to stop it spreading. Yvette's false eyelashes leave her with abrasions to her eyes.

episodes.name: Stronger Together
episodes.overview: 52-year-old John is airlifted to St George's after being accidentally hit in the face by a golf club and receiving a critical head injury. Joan, 77,  arrives in A&E after falling down the stairs at home and hurting her leg. Siobhan, who is 28, has cut her finger chopping vegetables.

episodes.name: Stiff Upper Lip
episodes.overview: Maura, 85, is rushed into St George's after being found face down on her bedroom floor. Mimi, who is 23 and a chef, is treated after cutting her thumb while chopping peppers at home. 37-year-old doctor Jim arrives in A&E after a collision with a van while he was cycling to work.

episodes.name: Forever Young
episodes.overview: 81-year-old cyclist Bill is brought to St George's from Surrey after being hit by a car. Amy, 93, arrives in A&E with her friend after a clothes airer fell on top of her while she was hanging out the washing. Samuel, who is 78, has hurt his face after tripping over some boxes while shopping.

episodes.name: Till Death Us Do Part
episodes.overview: Charulata, 59, is rushed to A&E after collapsing at home with signs of a stroke. 75-year-old Anne comes to St George's after falling and hurting her elbow on holiday. Luke, who is 28 and has epilepsy, arrives after cutting his finger at work, and he is worried it may trigger a seizure.

episodes.name: Training Day
episodes.overview: 77-year-old Martin is rushed to St George's after suffering multiple seizures. Lilly, 6, has cut her head after falling off her scooter. Harry, who is 83, arrives with shortness of breath and chest pains after collapsing while shopping.

episodes.name: Daddy's Girl
episodes.overview: 10-year-old Ashleigh is rushed to St George's by ambulance after twisting her leg while playing football. 3-year-old Lola visits A&E with her dad after having a seizure. 91-year-old Betty arrives with severe chest pain.

episodes.name: Work Hard, Play Hard
episodes.overview: 54-year-old Mary is rushed to St George's after she collapsed in the street and hit her head. Jessica, 27, has a wound that will not heal, after having a lumpectomy to remove breast cancer tissue two months ago. Robert, who is 37, arrives in A&E after colliding with a car on his motorbike.

episodes.name: New Horizons
episodes.overview: 5-year-old Isa is rushed to A&E after being hit by a car and trapped underneath it. Donald, who is 85 and a retired actor, comes to the hospital with pain in his bladder. Tom, 26, is treated after slicing his leg with a circular saw.

episodes.name: Heartbreak
episodes.overview: 75-year-old Gerry is rushed to A&E with a dangerously high heart rate of over 250bpm, and doctors suspect an underlying chest infection is the cause. Margaret, who is 92, arrives at St Georges after falling over and hitting her head. Daniel, 6, is treated for an infected blister on his foot.

episodes.name: Through Thick and Thin
episodes.overview: 13-year-old Tom is rushed to St George's after crashing his bike head first into a parked car while racing a friend. 26-year-old Andy comes to A&E after injuring his knee during a game of Frisbee. 51-year-old Jason arrives after suffering from blurred vision for two days.

episodes.name: Coming Home
episodes.overview: 43-year-old cyclist John is brought to A&E after crashing face first into a car, with injuries are so severe that he was put into an induced coma at the scene. Pat, who is 68, awaits the results of an X-ray after injuring her leg on holiday. Adrian, 89, has severe chest pain.

episodes.name: Quality of Life
episodes.overview: Barrie, 78, is rushed in with breathing difficulties and tests reveal he has fluid on his lungs and faces serious medical treatment. 75-year-old David is treated after falling down a flight of stairs. 82-year-old Bob is admitted after a DIY accident at home.

episodes.name: Love Thy Neighbour
episodes.overview: Andy, 48, is rushed in after falling 12 feet from a tree while cutting branches, badly fracturing both ankles. Angela, 59, has come to St George's as her heart has been beating at over 150bpm for eight hours. 3-year-old Shane has fallen off his grandma's trampoline.

episodes.name: Only Yesterday
episodes.overview: Janine, 44, is rushed to St George's after being kicked by a horse at her stables in Surrey, and had to crawl over two fields to call for help.

episodes.name: Keep on Going
episodes.overview: Liam, 31, is rushed to St George's after collapsing at home after his fourth epileptic seizure of the day. 89-year-old Mair is brought to A&E with severe chest pain and difficulty breathing. 12-year-old Lauren arrives by ambulance after breaking her leg while scoring a try in a rugby match.

episodes.name: Here We Go Again...
episodes.overview: Stephan, who is 39, is rushed to St George's with internal bleeding from his femoral artery, caused by complications following an angiogram he had the day before. Emmanuel Jr, 19, arrives in A&E after suffering an acute sickle cell crisis. 40-year-old Fernanda is admitted with abdominal pain, but the test results reveal a surprising reason for her discomfort.

episodes.name: Dangerous Pursuits
episodes.overview: Motorcyclist Michelle, 50, is rushed to A&E after crashing head first into a lamp post. Timothy, who is 69, arrives at St George's after riding his bicycle into the back of a parked ambulance. 33-year-old expectant mother Eleanor is admitted after cutting her thumb on a meat cleaver.

episodes.name: Lonely Hearts
episodes.overview: Beth, who is 68, is rushed to St George's after falling down a flight of stairs and badly breaking her ankle. Leigh, 67, is admitted with head injuries after being knocked off his bicycle in a hit-and-run incident. 26-year-old Luke arrives in A&E after an accident at work involving an electric saw.

episodes.name: Love's Sacrifice
episodes.overview: Cyclist Athar, who is 22, is rushed to St George's after a collision with a car on his way to work.

episodes.name: You Only Live Once
episodes.overview: 11-year-old Jack is rushed to A&E after being hit by a motorbike while walking to his first day at secondary school.

episodes.name: The Handover
episodes.overview: 71-year-old Tony is rushed to St George's by air ambulance after falling head first onto a tiled floor while doing some DIY in his kitchen. Charlie was assaulted on his way home from a night out. Lucy, 10, has been having seizures for 48 hours.

episodes.name: One False Move
episodes.overview: 12-year-old Tulsi is airlifted to St George's after falling from a cliff near her home in Hastings. Bus driver Adam, 39, faces lengthy emergency surgery after his motorbike collided with a car.

episodes.name: Someone To Watch Over Me
episodes.overview: Mel, 71, is rushed to St George's after being accidentally knocked down and run over by her husband John. Maddi, who is 4, has fallen and injured her neck on a train.

episodes.name: Dear Heart
episodes.overview: Mark, who is 52, is rushed to St George's by air after a road traffic collision threw him from his motorbike and left him suffering a cardiac arrest. Kayley, 25, has fallen from her horse and doctors worry she's dislocated her hip.

episodes.name: Never Say Die
episodes.overview: 80-year-old Frances is rushed to St George's by air ambulance after falling backwards into her empty swimming pool. Ruth, 86, is rushed in with her heart beating three times the normal rate. Jerry, who is 20, has crashed her car coming back from a party at 5am.

episodes.name: Time of our Lives
episodes.overview: John, who is 84, is rushed to St George's after losing control of his car and crashing into a road sign. Reggie, 7, has broken his arm while doing a cartwheel to celebrate England beating Wales at Euro 2016.

episodes.name: Time's Arrow
episodes.overview: Nicky, who is 61, is airlifted to St George's by helicopter after a car mounted the pavement at 30mph and ran her over while she was out walking. 91-year-old Sam arrives in resus after a suspected stoke. Baby Teddy has fallen out of his car seat face-first onto concrete.

episodes.name: Face Value
episodes.overview: 70-year-old George is rushed to A&E after he fell and impaled his eye on a piece of driftwood. Debby, who is 59, has cut her hand in her lawnmower while removing some grass cuttings. Phoebe, 8, has scissors stuck in her thigh.

episodes.name: You've Got a Friend in Me
episodes.overview: 60-year-old bricklayer Phil is rushed to A&E in a critical condition after falling just two feet off a ladder at work and suffering multiple injuries. Violet, who is 93, has fallen and seriously fractured her leg.

episodes.name: In Sickness and in Health
episodes.overview: Corey, who is 27, is rushed to St George's after suffering a cardiac arrest during a game of ice hockey. John, 55, fell 10 feet while taking down scaffolding at home.

episodes.name: You Raise Me Up
episodes.overview: Michelle, who is 54, is airlifted to St George's after being involved in a car crash with her husband Paul in Surrey. Derren, 41, has fractured his ankle while trampolining with his daughter.

episodes.name: Made of Steel
episodes.overview: Mohammed, who is 64, has been hit by a pizza delivery motorbike. 90-year-old John comes to St George's after his GP picked up on his abnormally low heart rate.

episodes.name: Flying Solo
episodes.overview: Aaron, who is 31, is rushed to St George's after overturning his car onto metal railings during a high-speed collision. Fiona, 65, is rushed to St George's after falling over in a restaurant and cutting her knee during her friend's 70th birthday party.

episodes.name: The Tree of Life
episodes.overview: Neil, who is 84 and has a heart condition, has fallen down the stairs at home and damaged his shoulder. Danny, 25, has been knocked off his motorbike, receiving a serious leg fracture. Adil has twisted his knee playing badminton.

episodes.name: Carpe Diem
episodes.overview: Niki, who is 34, is airlifted to St George's after he crashed into another rider during a charity bike ride. Peter, 90, has blood poisoning.

episodes.name: Catch Me If I Fall
episodes.overview: Valerie, who is 63, is rushed to St George's after falling from a horse. Natasha has damaged her leg while trampolining at her son's birthday party. Lisa, 66, fell on her kitchen floor and may have damaged her prosthetic hip.

episodes.name: Flesh and Blood
episodes.overview: Pam, who is 53, is rushed to A&E after suffering a suspected heart attack. 10-year-old Cora is rushed to St George's after being thrown from a horse into the low hanging branches of a tree.

episodes.name: Safe From Harm
episodes.overview: 51-year-old painter and decorator Gary is rushed to St George's after falling ten feet from a ladder. Beatriz, who is 5, has a rare kidney condition that affects her immune system. A dementia patient has had a suspected stroke.

episodes.name: Sweethearts
episodes.overview: 40-year-old Adrian is escalated from majors to resus after crashing his bike into a car. Graham, 54, has stubbed his toe trying to not tread on his friend's cat. Steve, who is 49, has been brought to A&E after his heart rate more than doubled in an hour.

episodes.name: Against All Odds
episodes.overview: 20-year-old Antonio is rushed to A&E after a motorcycle accident. Karen, 40, has fallen off her horse, which then trampled on her. Hayley, who is 29, comes to St George's after experiencing an infection and low immune system.

episodes.name: Stand By Your Man
episodes.overview: A CT scan reveals some unexpected news for lorry driver Neil, 52, who's fallen off a ramp. 28-year-old Ben has dislocated his shoulder in a cycling accident. Wendy, 73, has a severe open ankle fracture after falling at home.

episodes.name: Boys Will Be Boys
episodes.overview: 30-year-old Chris has sustained a potentially life-threatening wound after his friend fired the inside shaft of a biro pen from an air rifle, deep into Chris's abdomen. Student Lennon has injured his head after jumping into a door frame while kicking a balloon. Stafford's cardiac defibrillator keeps shocking him.

episodes.name: Candle in the Wind
episodes.overview: 8-year-old Billy is rushed to St George's after being crushed by falling bricks that were being stored on his front drive. Luther, who is 6, has a metal washer stuck on his finger. Audrey, 83, has hurt her wrist in a fall while on holiday.

episodes.name: Just Seventeen
episodes.overview: 17-year-old Shea has serious stab wounds and is sent to a high dependency unit. Bob, also 17, arrives after impaling his leg on a fence while taking a shortcut home from his school. 33-year-old James is brought in by ambulance after fainting at home.

episodes.name: Love Through the Ages
episodes.overview: Judith, who is 79, is airlifted to St George's after being involved in a road traffic collision. Mohammad, 80, has fallen at home while celebrating Eid.

episodes.name: Growing Pains
episodes.overview: Lewis, who is 18, has come off a motorbike and collided with two cars. Sam, 27, fainted and cut his lips while smoking a Cuban cigar at a barbecue.

episodes.name: Road to Freedom
episodes.overview: Michelle, who is 49, is rushed to St George's after colliding with a car on a dual carriageway. Frankie, 19, has been thrown from her horse. 11-year-old Merlin has hurt his wrist.

episodes.name: Game of Chance
episodes.overview: David, who is 29, is airlifted to St George's following a head on collision at speed. An 18-year-old breaks his leg playing football. A great-grandmother falls down the stairs.

episodes.name: Lost and Found
episodes.overview: Kim, who is 58, has been run over by a lorry and suffered severe blood loss. Patrick, 65, has fallen from a loft ladder.

episodes.name: Special Relationships
episodes.overview: Lee, who is 36, is rushed to St George's after being involved in a high-speed road traffic collision. 34-year-old Jeroen has been knocked off his bike. Chris, who is 21 years old and a vlogger, has dislocated his finger playing basketball.

episodes.name: Broken Heart
episodes.overview: Joan, who is 80, has severe pain in her chest, arm and jaw. Roofer Mark, 54, has fallen 10 feet off a ladder. Josie fell and hit her head while performing a Dirty Dancing routine on a hen do.

episodes.name: Forget Me Not
episodes.overview: Emma, who is 47, needs a CT scan following a cycling collision with a bus. 33-year-old Josh has severe back pain. Pamela, 87, is worried that she may have a blood clot in her leg.

episodes.name: My Guiding Star
episodes.overview: Mike, who is 79, collapsed in the street while walking his dog. Andrew, 53, tripped on a paving slab on his way to work and has a suspected dislocated shoulder.

episodes.name: Supporting Cast
episodes.overview: 64-year-old John is brought to St George's in an induced coma, having been thrown from his bicycle at high speed. Florian, who is 21 and a drama student, tripped and hurt his foot rushing to class. Ron, 82, is rushed to A&E with a critically low heart rate of under 40 beats per minute.

episodes.name: Love Conquers All
episodes.overview: Stuart, who is 40, is transferred from another hospital after being involved in a high-speed collision with multiple cyclists during a race. Elicia-Jean, 83, collapsed at home after experiencing dizziness from a suspected infection.

episodes.name: The Unknown
episodes.overview: An unknown patient arrives after collapsing and falling face first in the street. 29-year-old Rick comes to minors after an accident at the gym. Marigold, 3, has signs of a chest infection.

episodes.name: Bringing Up Baby
episodes.overview: Marie, who is 31, arrives in A&E by ambulance after collapsing at home with an unexplained headache. 10-month-old Erin has a build-up of wax in her ears following a cold and fever. Eileen, 87, comes in with shortness of breath and a high heart rate.

episodes.name: Wrong Place, Wrong Time
episodes.overview: This shocking episode follows three middle-aged women who are stabbed in broad daylight in a random attack at a supermarket car park in Surrey. Jean, who's 67, had gone to Sainsbury's to get macaroni cheese for her grandson and was stabbed in the back while carrying shopping to her car. Doctors are worried that the wound may have hit a vital organ or a major vessel and she's sent for urgent CT scans. Meanwhile, her daughter Clair recalls growing up in a pub in Fulham where her mum was the landlady: 'I remember a couple of guys came in with machetes yelling and shouting and she gave them a jolly good talking to... she's always been feisty... she can throw someone on the floor if she needs to'. Rani, who's 71, was stabbed twice in the back while waiting for a bus.

episodes.name: Unconditional Love
episodes.overview: Gary, who is 50, is brought in by ambulance after a garage collapsed and fell on his legs. Maggie, 83, comes in to A&E with suspected sepsis. Baby George comes in with his mum after drinking nail varnish remover.

episodes.name: Shelter From The Storm
episodes.overview: Adam, 20, is brought in by ambulance after being involved in a high-speed motorcycle accident. 70-year-old Richard comes to A&E with a high heart rate. Pia, who is 10, has fallen and hurt her knee.

episodes.name: Collision Course
episodes.overview: Motorcyclist Leon, 36, is airlifted to St George's after being involved in a head-on collision with a car. Graham, who is 37, has collided with another player while playing rugby and has lost feeling in his arms and legs. 4-year-old Elliott has pushed a stone up his nose to hide it from his sister.

episodes.name: Out of the Fire
episodes.overview: Evadney, 56, walks into A&E after badly burning her arm when an aerosol exploded in a bonfire that she was standing close to. Sufia, who is 5, is rushed to St George's by ambulance with head and scalp injuries after she was dragged under a car while she was on her way to school. 70-year-old Pat arrives after the car that she was driving hit a wall at speed.

episodes.name: The Courage To Go On
episodes.overview: Zach, 25, is rushed to A&E after completely severing four fingers in a building site accident. Ricky, who is 85, has hurt her back after falling at home. 10-year-old Daquon was hit by a motorbike while on his way to school and has a badly broken arm.

episodes.name: Lost for Words
episodes.overview: 54-year-old Richard arrives in A&E suffering symptoms of a suspected stroke. Peter, who is 76, arrives in A&E with a severe head injury, but it's not clear what exactly has happened to him.

episodes.name: Every Cloud...
episodes.overview: Maria, who is 52, suffers from MS and has been brought to resus with suspected sepsis. 6-year-old Grace has tissue stuck in her ear. Eve, 83, has fallen down the stairs.

episodes.name: Born To Be Wild
episodes.overview: Megan, 20, is rushed to St George's after being involved in a high-speed car crash. James, who is 78, has suspected internal bleeding.

episodes.name: The Underdogs
episodes.overview: Tony, 48, and his father have been in a motorbike crash. Alison has a broken leg from a horse riding accident. Harry, who is 12, has been in a 10-bike pile-up at a velodrome.

episodes.name: Liberation Day
episodes.overview: Tim came off his bike and has suspected spinal injuries. Jeanette is struggling to breathe. Mollie, who is 91, is in A&E after her daughter accidentally crashed into a lamp post.

episodes.name: The Good Fight
episodes.overview: Hussnain is rushed to A&E after being caught up in a accident involving a police car chasing another vehicle. Wrestler Kieran comes in after injuring his knee in a bout.

episodes.name: Child at Heart
episodes.overview: Billy, who is 25, is brought to St George's by helicopter after a van ran over his chest in a motorcycle accident. 2-year-old Freddie has jammed his thumb in a door. Stephen has shown signs of a stroke.

episodes.name: Live for Today
episodes.overview: Mark, 51, is brought to resus after coming off his bike. Dibs, who is 60, has fallen 10 feet off a balcony onto concrete. 10-year-old Aiden comes to paediatrics after hurting his foot on the monkey bars at school.

episodes.name: Safe Haven
episodes.overview: Judy, who is 72, is airlifted to St George's after being trampled by a herd of cows while she was walking her dog. Tamzen, who is 13, has broken her leg at trampoline practice at school. 18-year-old art student Hermione has cut her hand on a glass at her part-time waitressing job.

episodes.name: Someone To Come Home To
episodes.overview: Richard, who's 47, has fallen off a ladder while he was fixing his roof. 87-year-old Doreen arrives in resus suffering from a serious infection. 5-year-old Cojo has come to paediatrics after injuring his elbow while he was wrestling with his brother.

episodes.name: A Stubborn Kind of Fellow
episodes.overview: John has been in a cycling accident and was unconscious for 10 minutes. Sydney has severe chest pains. Alan has fallen and fractured his elbow.

episodes.name: Heart of the Home
episodes.overview: Lillian has extremely low blood pressure, and doctors discover that she is in the latter stages of pancreatic cancer. Carolyn bruised her neck and face when she slipped on wet decking. Dennis is having difficulty breathing.

episodes.name: In The Line Of Duty

episodes.name: Heavens Above
episodes.overview: 48-year-old paraglider pilot Martin is airlifted to St George's after a gust of wind threw him into a cliff. Eddie has been weakened by chemotherapy and has severe sepsis. Graham's nose will not stop bleeding.

episodes.name: Moving On Up

episodes.name: A Friend in Need
episodes.overview: Glyn is brought in after his leg is run over by a three tonne digger. John, who is 93 and has severe sepsis, is admitted after a fall at home. A toddler is brought in with diarrhoea.

episodes.name: Down to Earth
episodes.overview: Stephen, 48, has severely damaged his ankle after coming off his bike deep in the woods. Derek has had a suspected stroke. Bridget broke her wrist on a mountain path in Greece.

episodes.name: Love's Young Dream
episodes.overview: Neil is rushed in with severe chest and lung injuries after coming off his bike. Michael is brought in with chest problems after collapsing on a golf course. George has grazed his eye on a branch.

episodes.name: Value of Life
episodes.overview: Rich has been in a high speed car crash and cannot move his legs. Justin has a potentially life-threatening bleed on his brain following a football accident.

episodes.name: Mother's Courage
episodes.overview: Jacob, who is 20, has crashed his car into a wall at high speed and has suspected internal bleeding. Joan, who is 82, has fallen down the stairs. Young Jackson has a suspected infection on his cheek.

episodes.name: Inside Out
episodes.overview: Clive has breathing difficulties. Samuel has crashed his motorbike. 2-year-old Florence's parents think she has swallowed a coin.

episodes.name: To Have and To Hold
episodes.overview: Nikkita, who's 27, comes to A&E with her father after having a severe epileptic fit. Plumber Sebastian has sliced the tops of his fingers off at work.

episodes.name: A Job for Life

episodes.name: I Will Survive

episodes.name: Acts of Love

episodes.name: A Change Is Gonna Come
episodes.overview: Sergio, who's 44 and Alan, who's 71, have both been badly injured in cycling accidents.

episodes.overview: Nicole has burnt her foot with caustic soda. Francis, 28, fell off his bike and is suffering amnesia.

episodes.name: A Road Less Travelled
episodes.overview: Paul, 60, has been in a collision with a van. Jeremy, who is 4 and has a series of chronic conditions including microcephaly and epilepsy, is struggling to breathe.

episodes.name: From This Day Forward
episodes.overview: David has fallen from a ladder. John has fallen down stairs.

episodes.overview: Benoit, who is 9, has abdominal pains and doctors are concerned that it may be appendicitis. Michelle has suspected sepsis. Charley-Ann has part of an earring stuck in her ear.

episodes.name: I'll Stand By You

episodes.name: Too Close for Comfort
episodes.overview: Brooke, who is 12, has gone into respiratory arrest after having a severe asthma attack. 76-year-old Howard has burns on his face and hands from trying to put out an explosion in his shed. Cyclist Colin has fractured his collarbone.

episodes.name: The Kids Are Alright

episodes.name: Fix You
episodes.overview: Greg has been knocked off his motorbike and has critical injuries to his arm and leg. Cara, who is 11, has fallen from a human pyramid doing gymnastics and has a badly broken arm.

episodes.name: You're All I Need To Get By
episodes.overview: Paul, who is 66, is brought to A&E with a dangerously high heart rate. Nicky, 48, has a swelling in her throat. 7-year-old Kit has injured his chest in a golf buggy.

episodes.name: The Survivors
episodes.overview: Ranjan, 64, is brought to St George's after losing control of her car and colliding with a tree. Callum, who is 20, has mysteriously collapsed. 4-year-old Scarlett has hurt her leg in an accident.

episodes.name: Call Of Duty
episodes.overview: Jahan, 58, has severe chest pains, which doctors think could be a heart attack. Arthur, who is 92, is rushed to A&E after he fell and hit his head at his care home.

episodes.name: Children of Men
